result.execSummary:
Jorge L Aponte-Montanez was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Jorge L Aponte-Montanez was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Attorney Mary Garvin Guimont in court, defendant Jorge L Aponte-Montanez not in court, in custody.  Grant Ian Huebner appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Attorney appeared by video means.  Defendant has been turned over to the State of New York on 2/24/2022.
On motion of the state, Court ordered case closed.

Defendant Jorge L Aponte-Montanez in court with attorney Mary Garvin Guimont.  Defendant Jorge L Aponte-Montanez in custody.  Francesco Mineo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Jorge L Aponte-Montanez appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Shelton, Branch 40.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of rights and right to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus.  Court found the defendant is the person wanted in the State of New York.  Defendant waived extradition.  Signed Waiver of Extradition received and filed.  Court ordered the defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/0a25f782-7319-dd31-4ed9-c0f452a2bc2b  Status conference scheduled for March 11, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
